<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="soft-adj">soft <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /sɒft/    美 /sɔːft/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-hard">1.★ <strong>柔软的【反:hard】；柔和的；轻柔的；</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>soft skin
柔滑的肌肤</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>soft light / colors
柔和的灯光/颜色</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>soft music
轻柔的音乐</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>(饮料) 不含酒精的；(水) 不含无机盐的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>soft drinks
软饮料(不含酒精的饮料)</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>(天气等) 温暖的；和煦的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is used to the soft climate of the south.
他习惯于南方温暖的气候。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>温柔的；宽厚的；和蔼的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>have a soft heart
有一副软心肠</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>soften /'sɒfn/ v <br />
softly /'sɒftli/ adv   </p></div>